=3D"302" width=3D"324"></figure><a name=3D"anchor-7"></a><h4>Circumcircle a=
nd incircle</h4><p>In any regular n-gon, a circle can be drawn that passes =
through all vertices. This is the cirmuscribed circle or <strong>circumcirc=
le</strong>.&nbsp;The center of this circle is the center of the n-gon. The=
 radius of circumcircle <span class=3D"mjpage"><svg xmlns:xlink=3D"http://w=
ww.w3.org/1999/xlink" width=3D"2.708ex" height=3D"2.509ex" style=3D"vertica=
