the height is perpendicular to it. Universal formulas for these dimensions =
are not possible though. A methodology can be improvised however, based on =
the value of N.</p><figure class=3D"image"><img src=3D"https://cdn.calcreso=
urce.com/images/geom-ngon-bbox.rev.c7bb8b738b.png" loading=3D"lazy" height=
